Another question is, here I just ask user to provide a callable object that takes model and dataloader as input. Should I impose certain restrictions on this behavior, for example, given a Base class and ask user to inherit this class to implement custom logic?
```python
class BaseMetric(metaclass=ABCMeta):
    def __init__(self, metric: Callable):
        self.metric = metric
    
    @abstractmethod
    def __call__(self, model: nn.Module, data_loader: DataLoader = None):
        pass

class CustomMetric(BaseMetric):
    def __init__(self, metric: Callable):
        self.metric = metric
    
    def __call__(self, model: nn.Module, data_loader: DataLoader = None):
        # custom logic
        pass

metric = Accuracy()
metric = CustomMetric(metric)
```

